Sentece: From pharmacokinetic studies, circulating half-life of corifollitropin alfa was calculated to be 17.3h in rats and 46.9h in dogs, 1.5- to 2-fold longer than recombinant FSH.
Title: Pharmacologic profiling of corifollitropin alfa, the first developed sustained follicle stimulant.
Name: Lutropin alfa
